The photo was not taken in 2019 and does: It was taken in 2015 and shows a shantytown in Paris along a disused railway line.
A reverse: image search of the photo led to a December 2015 Daily Mail article discussing the Roma community in Paris and their shacks built along the railway line.
The Petite Ceinture: the railway line depicted in the photo, has been derelict for several decades and its redevelopment has sparked debates in France.
The camp in the photo: which housed approximately 350 people, took root around the time of the migrant crisis in Europe in 2015.
